 Hamisu Wadume, the Kidnap Kingpin at the centre of a clash between the Nigerian Police Force and Nigerian Army has been arrested. According to Premiumtimes, Wadume was sighted at the Police Force headquarters in Abuja on Tuesday. Mr Wadume was the ‘high profile’ kidnapping suspect arrested by the police on August 6. He was being driven to Jalingo by the police team when soldiers opened fire on them along Ibi-Wukari Road, killing three police officers and a civilian. More details soon… The post Taraba Kidnap Kingpin, Hamisu Wadume Arrested appeared first on . Source: 36Ng